Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to moderate turn. Button stamp with large central dot. Clay near fine purplish brown.
Production date: 213 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes (2015) 142.)
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (?)
Curator's comments: Name Charmokles. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0246.09.
Acquisition name: Donated by: Egypt Exploration Fund (Trimming points to the provenance)
